-- #873 (S0, CLOSED by PR #891): a body-local ambiguous Num literal in an
-- interface-default method was grounded to Int ONLY when the impl providing
-- that default lives in the SAME module as the interface (the specialized
-- impl path). `impl T Foo` lives HERE, in a DIFFERENT module from interface T
-- (tface.mdk), so the default is checked via the generic-default path, which
-- pre-#891 had no such grounding: the element var of `s [1, 2]` (in T's
-- default body) stayed unbound, `s` saw a receiver of `List _a`, and the
-- GENERAL `impl S (List a)` (999) was picked instead of the specific
-- `impl S (List Int)` (1) — a silent wrong VALUE, `check` green either way,
-- keyed purely on module placement. See test/eval_typed_modules_fixtures/
-- default_method_numlit_crossmodule/ for the real-prelude twin of this
-- fixture; this one runs the same shape through the eval/native/wasm
-- three-engine differential (test/diff_compiler_engines.sh) and native-only
-- emit gates (diff_compiler_llvm_modules.sh, selfcompile_emit.sh), which is
-- why it stays prelude-free (putStrLn/intToString, not println).
--
-- Must print 1. A regression to 999 means the generic-default path has again
-- lost the body-local Num grounding.
import tface.{T(..), t}

data Foo = Foo

impl T Foo where
  

main = putStrLn (intToString (t Foo))
